                          April 27 (Bloomberg) -- Doug Freedman, an analyst at Broadpoint AmTech Inc., talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about Texas Instruments Inc.'s performance and growth outlook.
     Texas Instruments, the second-largest U.S. chipmaker, predicted sales and profit that topped analysts’ estimates, helped by demand for semiconductors used in industrial machinery, phone networks and cars. Freedman, speaking from San Francisco, also discusses the outlook for Intel Corp. and the semiconductor industry. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
